title: 1 dead, 2 injured in Enid triple shooting
content:
ENID, Okla. —
Three people were shot and one person is in custody Saturday evening after a shooting in Enid, officials said.
The shooting was reported just before 6 p.m. in the 1800 block of West Maine Street, near Lincoln Street.
Police found a 17-year-old boy, a 18-year-old man and a 21-year-old woman with gunshot wounds, according to a news release.
The 17-year-old victim died at a hospital, the news release said. He has been identified as Daultn Dickerson.
The 18-year-old victim, identified as Jonathan Winters had two non-life-threatening injuries.
The woman is in critical condition. She was identified as Alissa Cull.
Police took Christopher Reynaud, 23, into custody at the scene. He faces charges of first-degree murder and shooting with intent to kill.
